#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.32"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.32:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.32:0.2"
msgid "4. Devadūtavagga "
msgstr "4. Messengers of the Gods "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.32:0.3"
msgid "32. Ānandasutta "
msgstr "32. With Ānanda "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an3.32:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.32:2.1"
msgid "“Siyā nu kho, bhante, bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā nāssu, bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā nāssu; "
msgstr "“Could it be, sir, that a mendicant might gain a state of immersion such that there’s no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for this conscious body; and no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for all external stimuli; "

msgctxt "an3.32:2.2"
msgid "yañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ upasampajja viharato ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na honti tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ upasampajja vihareyyā”ti? "
msgstr "and that they’d live having attained the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where ego, possessiveness, and underlying tendency to conceit are no more?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.32:2.3"
msgid "“Siyā, ānanda, bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā nāssu, bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā nāssu; "
msgstr "“It could be, Ānanda, that a mendicant gains a state of immersion such that they have no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for this conscious body; and no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for all external stimuli; "

msgctxt "an3.32:2.4"
msgid "yañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ upasampajja viharato ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na honti tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ upasampajja vihareyyā”ti. "
msgstr "and that they’d live having attained the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where ego, possessiveness, and underlying tendency to conceit are no more.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.32:3.1"
msgid "“Yathā kathaṃ pana, bhante, siyā bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā nāssu, bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā nāssu; "
msgstr "“But how could this be, sir?” "

msgctxt "an3.32:3.2"
msgid "yañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ upasampajja viharato ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na honti tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ upasampajja vihareyyā”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.133, sc4
msgctxt "an3.32:4.1"
msgid "“Idhānanda, bhikkhuno evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "“Ānanda, it’s when a mendicant thinks: "

msgctxt "an3.32:4.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ sabbasaṅkhārasamatho sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānan’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is peaceful; this is sublime—that is, the stilling of all activities, the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, fading away, cessation, extinguishment.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.32:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, ānanda, siyā bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā nāssu, bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā nāssu; "
msgstr "That’s how, Ānanda, a mendicant might gain a state of immersion such that there’s no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for this conscious body; and no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for all external stimuli; "

msgctxt "an3.32:4.4"
msgid "yañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ upasampajja viharato ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na honti tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ upasampajja vihareyyāti. "
msgstr "and that they’d live having achieved the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where ego, possessiveness, and underlying tendency to conceit are no more. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an3.32:5.1"
msgid "Idañca pana metaṃ, ānanda, sandhāya bhāsitaṃ pārāyane puṇṇakapañhe: "
msgstr "And Ānanda, this is what I was referring to in ‘The Way to the Beyond’, in ‘The Questions of Puṇṇaka’ when I said: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc6
#. VAR: paroparāni → parovarāni (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.32:6.1"
msgid "‘Saṅkhāya lokasmiṃ paroparāni, "
msgstr "‘Having surveyed the world high and low, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.32:6.2"
msgid "Yassiñjitaṃ natthi kuhiñci loke; "
msgstr "they’re not shaken by anything in the world. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: anīgho → anigho (s1-3, km, pts1) | anagho (?)
msgctxt "an3.32:6.3"
msgid "Santo vidhūmo anīgho nirāso, "
msgstr "Peaceful, unclouded, untroubled, with no need for hope—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.32:6.4"
msgid "Atāri so jātijaranti brūmī’”ti. "
msgstr "they’ve crossed over birth and old age, I declare.’” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.32:6.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

